tags: Thanks for the questions in return!
question: 🥊 💻 🎶 🎉 👪 👚 🎤 My turn! >3
answer:
Alrighty then, here goes.

🥊 : Favorite Ranked Mode?

That would probably go to Tower Control. ‘Cause I feel that it’s my best mode performance wise.

💻 : When did you start playing?

AAAAALL the way back during the first game’s first ever Testfire. I was pretty much hooked ever since.

🎶 : Squid Sisters or Off The Hook?

I’m sorry, I know this is gonna be a cop out, but I just can’t pick between the two of them. They both have their own style and their own positives that I can’t pick between them.

🎉 :  What do you want the next Splatfest theme to be?

Eehh I don’t know. I’m up for just about anything, really. Maybe a sponsored Splatfest or something. (My dream Splatfest is still Mario vs. Sonic, but I highly doubt it’s gonna happen next).

👪 : Favorite NPC?

Do the idols count? ‘Cause that’s what I’m going with. :P

👚 :  Favorite gear set?

(Old pic but) Squid Hair Clip, Basic Tee and Pink Trainers. Pretty basic I know, but it’s pretty much me in terms of fashion. This is also my Ranked Mode set up, and the only time I’ll mix outfit pieces away from the full set.

🎤 : Favorite band?

Turquoise October. Because I haven’t listened to them in game to the point where they pretty much become white noise (I’m sorry other bands, your songs are good, but…it’s the unfortunate truth). Also Shooting Starfish is my jam (especially the beginning).

summary: Scene from a commercial for the New Nintendo 3DS XL showing the functionality of the C-Stick to move the camera, featuring Mario...
caption:
Scene from a commercial for the New Nintendo 3DS XL showing the functionality of the C-Stick to move the camera, featuring Mario and Luigi. Of interest here is the blackboard, which depicts the musical staff for the Song of Time from The Legend of Zelda: Ocarina of Time, particularly the version of it used in the remake, The Legend of Zelda: Ocarina of Time 3D, where the lowest two notes (A and C-Down in the original, L and R in the remake) are represented by squares instead of by circles.
